==English==

===Etymology===
Around 1705-1715, borrowed from the French {{term|connoisseur|lang=frm}}, from the verb {{term|connoître|lang=fr}} (obsolete pre-1835 spelling of {{term|connaître|lang=fr||to know}}).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˌkɒnəˈsɜ/|/ˌkɒnəˈsʊə/}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# A [[specialist]] of a given field whose opinion is valued; especially in one of the [[fine arts]], or in a matter of [[taste]]
#* '''1883''', [[w:Robert Louis Stevenson|Robert Louis Stevenson]], ''[[w:Treasure Island|Treasure Island]]''
#*: This, when it was brought to him, he drank slowly, like a '''connoisseur''', lingering on the taste...

